    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">I threw this deck together in about 30 minutes.  It took awhile to cut the cards back.  IT was a 90 card deck...now it is 80.  Which is a TON of cards.  But the good thing is the amount of Companions and the amount of Minions.  Plus the support cards.  <br />
<br />
The Fellowship is meant to run...But they can fight, which is why used Valor and Strength of Arms.  Plus with Gimli support, with axe and hand axe and events.  He can beat just about anyone.  <br />
<br />
Shadow is meant to hurt and burdenize.  IF you can get enough burdens, which you can, your events become more useful.  I am looking to add more Easterlings - but I am really looking for input on the Southron part of the shadow.<br />
<br />
SO before you give me a bad rating...look through the cards and then reread my strategy...I am looking for more ideas on this type of Gimli/legolas deck.<br />
